WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.640
So the two approved ones and one in development, zilivertin and vedotin ADCs, they all have

00:00:09.640 --> 00:00:10.640
a common theme.

00:00:10.640 --> 00:00:15.460
They do lead to responses and we have invariably relapses.

00:00:15.460 --> 00:00:19.360
And so as single agents, they're not that helpful, but they're being used in combinations

00:00:19.360 --> 00:00:23.360
and they're used in situations where we need bridging to some other treatments such as

00:00:23.360 --> 00:00:25.700
bispecifics or CAR-Ts.

00:00:25.700 --> 00:00:29.880
So clearly there's a lot of room for improvement.

00:00:29.880 --> 00:00:39.220
So I asked my associate chat GPT to give me a little, of course with my instructions,

00:00:39.220 --> 00:00:44.640
to give a little picture of what is coming and what could be coming in the next generation

00:00:44.640 --> 00:00:46.700
of ADCs.

00:00:46.700 --> 00:00:55.840
So not to be left behind, there will be and there are bispecific ADCs that can go after

00:00:55.840 --> 00:00:56.920
two targets.

00:00:56.920 --> 00:00:59.760
There will be new warrants.

00:00:59.760 --> 00:01:08.220
New warheads, new delivery drugs, such as degraders, rather than just giving chemotherapeutics.

00:01:08.220 --> 00:01:17.140
You can combine the payloads, it doesn't have to be just one kind, the new site-specific

00:01:17.140 --> 00:01:21.140
conjugation methods being implied in a new targets.

00:01:21.140 --> 00:01:27.500
And one that I want to focus a little bit on is ROR1, so not a brand new target anymore,

00:01:27.500 --> 00:01:29.640
but it was identified.

00:01:29.640 --> 00:01:37.540
As an orphan receptor in 1992 by Dr. Kipps, it's now known that it's actually encoding

00:01:37.540 --> 00:01:40.720
a receptor for Win5A.

00:01:40.720 --> 00:01:46.120
What is interesting about it, it's an embryonic antigen that's expressed during embryogenesis,

00:01:46.120 --> 00:01:52.980
but virtually not at normal tissues in real life anymore, except when malignancies occur

00:01:52.980 --> 00:01:57.560
and cancer cells remind themselves of their maybe embryonic origin.

00:01:57.560 --> 00:01:59.520
So they do express to various degrees.

00:01:59.520 --> 00:02:05.040
ROR1, particularly heme malignancies, but across the board, many solid cancers do this

00:02:05.040 --> 00:02:06.420
as well.

00:02:06.420 --> 00:02:14.340
So Xiluvertimab-Vidotin was developed as an ADC targeting ROR1 and delivering the good

00:02:14.340 --> 00:02:16.340
old payload MMAE.

00:02:16.340 --> 00:02:24.820
It was initially developed by a company, Malus Bio, and it was taken over by Merck.

00:02:24.820 --> 00:02:29.400
So where is Xiluvertimab-Vidotin going these days?

00:02:29.400 --> 00:02:33.620
You see on the right side, it's single-agent activity in relapsed refractory large cell

00:02:33.620 --> 00:02:34.620
lymphoma.

00:02:34.620 --> 00:02:38.200
It does activity, but then rapid relapses.

00:02:38.200 --> 00:02:42.340
So there's activity in frontline trial development right now.

00:02:42.340 --> 00:02:50.360
There was a study of it in large cell lymphoma with 15 out of 15 patients responding.

00:02:50.360 --> 00:02:54.740
It was a short follow-up, reported at ASH24.

00:02:54.740 --> 00:02:59.280
In combination, it is compared with R-CHOP, so Xiluvertimab-Vidotin.

00:02:59.280 --> 00:03:08.220
Plus R-CHP versus R-CHOP, following the polar-tuzumab theme.

00:03:08.220 --> 00:03:15.840
But because there is polar-tuzumab, there's the study at the bottom, where the two ADCs,

00:03:15.840 --> 00:03:23.500
Polar and Xiluvertimab-Vidotin, are being compared, particularly in GCP DRPCRs, because Polar

00:03:23.500 --> 00:03:26.660
didn't improve outcomes in that setting.

00:03:26.660 --> 00:03:29.160
So that's where maybe there might be a niche for Xiluvertimab-Vidotin.

00:03:29.160 --> 00:03:40.780
Now, Immunome also has a ROR1 ADC, a new target, but also a new payload.

00:03:40.780 --> 00:03:45.840
So they're delivering a topoisomerase inhibitor.

00:03:45.840 --> 00:03:52.820
They have an undisclosed clevo linker, and they have a high load of drug-to-antibody

00:03:52.820 --> 00:03:54.180
of eight.

00:03:54.180 --> 00:03:59.040
So this ADC comes highly armed, and it's going on in trials right now.

00:03:59.040 --> 00:04:05.420
We're having it in startup at UCLA as well, so I look forward to testing this ADC as well.

00:04:05.420 --> 00:04:12.740
Now, Dennis Sleiman, our division chief at UCLA, has this TORA lab, and there they identified

00:04:12.740 --> 00:04:21.840
a G-protein coupler receptor that was specifically expressed in heme and lymphoid tissues as

00:04:21.840 --> 00:04:24.040
opposed to normal tissues.

00:04:24.040 --> 00:04:28.920
So highly expressed in B cells, NT cells, and myeloid cells.

00:04:28.920 --> 00:04:35.400
And the exact description of this G-protein coupler receptor is not public yet.

00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:40.800
You have to be under a CDA, and then you're known.

00:04:40.800 --> 00:04:46.420
If you look at different malignancies, it is highly expressed in AML and in large B

00:04:46.420 --> 00:04:54.060
cell informers, but not much in other malignancies, as you can see from this survey.

00:04:54.060 --> 00:04:58.800
If you look at a cell line bank.

00:04:58.800 --> 00:05:02.980
Sleiman lab has several hundred cell lines across the board.

00:05:02.980 --> 00:05:06.520
It's really expressed in myeloma, lymphoma, and AML.

00:05:06.520 --> 00:05:10.060
But that's it.

00:05:10.060 --> 00:05:19.280
Here you see a mouse model where mice-bearing human large lymphoma cells were treated with

00:05:19.280 --> 00:05:25.780
either a naked antibody or different doses of the ADC, and you could get to 100% tumor

00:05:25.780 --> 00:05:28.680
growth inhibition with the high ADC.

00:05:28.680 --> 00:05:32.940
And that's the highest load of the ADC.

00:05:32.940 --> 00:05:40.940
And so this study was just opened at UCLA, and we treated the first patients two weeks

00:05:40.940 --> 00:05:41.940
ago.

00:05:41.940 --> 00:05:51.020
It's the first in-human open-label TOL-5700 study, first in monotherapy and then also

00:05:51.020 --> 00:05:53.840
planned in combination with Vitaxa.

00:05:53.840 --> 00:05:58.560
Patients that are eligible for these studies are relapsed refractory non-Hodgkin lymphomas,

00:05:58.560 --> 00:06:02.640
including low-grade transformed and high-grade lymphomas.

00:06:02.640 --> 00:06:05.280
In part one, we're looking at dose finding.

00:06:05.280 --> 00:06:11.820
We don't require the targeted expression, but it will be a requirement for part two.

00:06:11.820 --> 00:06:20.220
So in part two, there will be dose expansions in de novo large lymphomas and mandelcellar

00:06:20.220 --> 00:06:27.400
lymphoma and follicular lymphomas, grade 1 to 3a, and then in part three, there are plans

00:06:27.400 --> 00:06:28.440
